cleanDesc: BMW M Performance Inconel Exhaust - E90 M3 (2008+)
short-description: With the racetrack and the street in mind, this new exhaust system is crafted from an extremely heat-resistant and lightweight chrome-nickel alloy called Inconel. This flow optimized exhaust system reduces exhaust backpressure and allows the M3s 414 horsepower V8 engine to produce an even more powerful sound. Inconels unique qualities allowed engineers to reduce the thickness of the tubing from 1.5mm to 0.8mm. This resulted in a weight reduction of approximately 40%, or about 20 lbs. when compared to the stock exhaust system. Inconel has also proven to be very corrosion resistant and has been used at the highest level of Motorsports. The M Performance Exhaust includes perforated inner pipes and polished titanium tips, which are laser engraved with the M logo. It represents the ultimate in technology and sportiness, accentuating the individual character of the BMW M3. The exhaust was developed using state-of-the art CAD and FEM technology ensuring optimum fit and OEM quality.     2008+    M3 Sedan

cleanDesc: Dinan Dual Exhaust Valve Remote Kit - F8X M2/M3/M4, F9X M5 M8 X3/X4/...
short-description: The Dinan Dual Exhaust Valve Remote Kit lets you override the factory exhaust valve operation and fully open (or close) the valve at the press of a button. Directly compatible with 'F' and 'G' chassis BMW's using dual electronic valves, the Dinan Dual Exhaust Valve Remote Kit is robust in its potential applications. Once installed simply press the top button of the supplied wireless remote to open the valves fully and enjoy maximum aural pleasure. Alternatively, when the need arises for the exhaust to be as quiet as possible, press the bottom button on the remote and the valves will close. This system works with both the factory exhaust and any aftermarket system that utilizes the factory electronic exhaust valve actuator. Tested and compatible valve actuators include BMW P/N's: 18307851568, 18308686640, 18308632154, and 18308623424 Features: Opens the factory electronic exhaust valves with the push of a button. Wirelessly remote controlled. Weatherproof housing. Extra length wiring harnesses for maximum application and routing versatility.

cleanDesc: E92 M3 Borla Aggressive Sport Exhaust - Rear Mufflers
short-description: rear mufflers    slip-on    quad round 90mm Borla angle cut      Unleash that M3's V8 burble with this Borla muffler system! The V8 M3 sounds sooo nice with this exhaust you'll wonder why BMW didn't spec it like this from the beginning. They didn't because they needed to make sure it was quiet enough for everyone. But if you have felt the sound is too quiet and distant this is the perfect M3 exhaust upgrade. Of the three systems that Borla makes, this is the middle spec. Borla builds their exhaust with the goal of enhancing the sound - not just making it outrageously loud. In fact, Borla exhausts are some of the quietest and most pleasing sounds of all of the aftermarket brands we have seen. The M3 Borla produces a deep rumble perfectly suited to the V8. It's a throaty sound that any American muscle car fan will appreciate. Yet it manages to be civilized and unobstrusive when needed. This system slips on after the factory resonator section for an easy install. The Borla mufflers and pipes weigh in at only 34lbs - almost half the weight of the stock system - which helps performance in all areas.   Every Borla is made with 304 stainless steel for the internals and muffler body. Unlike other systems that can use coated aluminum, mild steel, or 409 stainless, the Borla uses true 304 stainless on the inside as well as the outside. This prevents the muffler from rusting and deteriorating from the inside out. Borla guarantees every muffler with a 1,000,000 mile warranty. Turner Motorsport has been the leading Borla dealer for BMW exhausts since we sold our first system in 1996, including using Borla Exhausts on every Turner BMW racecar.     2008-2013    M3 coupe

short-description: rear mufflers    slip-on    quad round 90mm Borla angle cut      This is the most aggressive muffler section that Borla produces for the E90/E92 M3. Their ATAK system -   costically   uned   pplied   inetics - allows a very high volume without drone and distortion. This is beyond your the usual 'muscle car' sound - this is full blown automotive thunder! Borla manages the sound waves inside the exhaust to produce an exhaust note that maintains its tone as revs rise. With ATAK, the sound output is tuned like a graphic equalizer to shape and focus sound waves for optimum high-volume output. This exclusive technology produces the highest available dB (decibel) levels in the Borla street-legal lineup, and is designed for high-performance purists who prefer exhaust notes over their stereos. For an exhaust that really emphasizes the M3's motorsport background this is THE exhaust system.    Every Borla is made with 304 stainless steel for the internals and muffler body. Unlike other systems that can use coated aluminum, mild steel, or 409 stainless, the Borla uses true 304 stainless on the inside as well as the outside. This prevents the muffler from rusting and deteriorating from the inside out. Borla guarantees every muffler with a 1,000,000 mile warranty.
